3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-72208-20%26h%3D6eb5c16a5126a7730d0d788b0833bd663ddeeb24ab838f55d5ced1601e28fda7%26postID%3D66c64e5871b62b11ae83b933%26postSlug%3Dlockheed-potentially-developing-sr72-hypersonic-spy-plane-secret-2024-8%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSkunk-Works-Personal-Memoir-Lockheed%252Fdp%252F0316743003%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBen%20Rich%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20accounts%20of%20several%20Skunk%20Works%20programs%2C%20like%20the%20D-21%20supersonic%20ISR%20drone%2C%20that%20began%20as%20a%20bright%20idea%20Lockheed's%20engineers%20knew%20the%20US%20military%20or%20intelligence%20apparatus%20could%20very%20likely%20use%2C%20and%20which%20were%20then%20developed%20and%20pitched%20to%20decision-makers%20at%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223122%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Lockheed%20M-21%20stealth%20reconnaissance%20plane%20in%20flight%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659bb91c1c5c7b8c9a0eb195%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Lockheed%20M-21%20stealth%20reconnaissance%20plane%20in%20flight%20over%20the%20Mojave%20Desert.%3Cp%3EMuseum%20of%20Flight%20Foundation%2FCORBIS%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20frequently%2C%20however%2C%20developmental%20efforts%20were%20spurred%20by%20hushed%20conversations%20between%20men%20like%20Kelly%20Johnson%20and%20senior%20Defense%20officials%20who%20relayed%20the%20nation's%20most%20pressing%20needs%20hoping%20the%20Skunk%20Works%20hive%20mind%20might%20have%20a%20potential%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFamously%2C%20Johnson%20designed%20and%20delivered%20America's%20first-ever%20jet-powered%20fighter%20in%20this%20manner%2C%20with%20formal%20design%20work%20on%20the%20XP-80%20commencing%20a%20full%20four%20months%20before%20the%20firm%20was%20awarded%20a%20contract%20for%20the%20jet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20this%20modern%20era%20of%20bureaucratic%20oversight%20and%20extended%20design%20cycles%2C%20it%20seems%20unlikely%20that%20Lockheed%20Martin%20would%20have%20gone%20all-in%20on%20fielding%20the%20SR-72%20without%20some%20pretty%20conclusive%20evidence%20from%20the%20Air%20Force%20that%20it'd%20eventually%20step%20in%20and%20foot%20the%20bill.%20The%20firm's%20financial%20records%20seem%20to%20substantiate%20that%20likelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20monitor%20the%20recoverability%20of%20pre-contract%20costs%2C%20which%20could%20be%20impacted%20by%20the%20customer's%20decision%20regarding%20future%20phases%20of%20the%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20Lockheed%20said%20of%20this%20program%20in%20its%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20SR-72%20effort%20appears%20to%20have%20continued%20to%20progress%20under%20the%20classified%20veil%20since%20early%202018%2C%20word%20of%20these%20losses%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20rapid%20expansion%20of%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20Skunk%20Works%20facilities%20and%20personnel%2C%20all%20point%20toward%20the%20production%20of%20a%20new%20classified%20aircraft%20meant%20not%20for%20testing%2C%20but%20likely%2C%20operational%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228689ca38-5861-40a1-b776-eb77c4d750c7%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20the%20SR-72%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FxbqWdXzV-Bk%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Heritage%20Today%20-%20ISR%20and%20Innovation%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%20began%20development%20on%20a%20hypersonic%20successor%20to%20the%20Blackbird%20in%202006.%20The%20program%20continued%20in%20secret%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20before%20being%20formally%20announced%20to%20the%20public%20in%202013%20with%20a%20media%20push%20that%20included%20several%20interviews%20with%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20hypersonics%20program%20manager%20and%20the%20engineer%20who%20led%20the%20effort%20for%20the%20previous%20seven%20years%2C%20Brad%20Leland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHypersonic%20aircraft%2C%20coupled%20with%20hypersonic%20missiles%2C%20could%20penetrate%20denied%20airspace%20and%20strike%20at%20nearly%20any%20location%20across%20a%20continent%20in%20less%20than%20an%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20Leland%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20in%20a%20Lockheed%20Martin%20press%20release%20that%20has%20since%20been%20taken%20down.%20%26quot%3BSpeed%20is%20the%20next%20aviation%20advancement%20to%20counter%20emerging%20threats%20in%20the%20next%20several%20decades.%20The%20technology%20would%20be%20a%20game-changer%20in%20theater%2C%20similar%20to%20how%20stealth%20is%20changing%20the%20battle%20space%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20high-speed%20aircraft%20would%20make%20use%20of%20a%20never-before-fielded%20type%20of%20engine%20that%20was%2C%20for%20all%20intents%20and%20purposes%2C%20two%20(or%20maybe%20even%20three)%20types%20of%20jet%20engines%20in%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Leland%20described%20it%2C%20this%20new%20propulsion%20system%20started%20with%20a%20conventional%20turbofan%20engine%20%E2%80%94%20either%20the%20Pratt%20%26amp%3B%20Whitney%20F100%20or%20the%20General%20Electric%20F110%20%E2%80%94%20as%20its%20basis.%20This%20turbofan%20would%20allow%20the%20aircraft%20to%20take%20off%20from%20a%20stop%20and%20accelerate%20to%20supersonic%20speeds%20like%20any%20normal%20fighter%2C%20but%20once%20the%20jet%20began%20to%20approach%20Mach%203%2C%20the%20engine's%20second%20half%20would%20roar%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20X-43A%20airplane%20is%20propelled%20by%20its%20supersonic%20combustion%20ramjet.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c654b1b4912df3ae1d99d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22787%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20X-43A%20airplane%20is%20propelled%20by%20its%20supersonic%20combustion%20ramjet.%3Cp%3ENASA%20Photo%20by%20Jim%20Ross%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20second%20half%20is%20said%20to%20be%20a%20dual-mode%20ramjet%20(sometimes%20called%20a%20dual-mode%20scramjet%20or%20supersonic%20combustion%20ramjet)%20that%20relies%20on%20the%20immense%20pressure%20of%20inflowing%20air%20at%20supersonic%20speeds%20and%20a%20variable%20inlet%20design%20to%20create%20intentionally%20placed%20shockwaves%20for%20compression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20this%20engine%20design%20could%20propel%20an%20aircraft%20well%20past%20the%20SR-71's%20record-setting%20top%20speed%20of%20Mach%203.2%2C%20past%20the%20notional%20hypersonic%20barrier%20at%20Mach%205%2C%20and%20potentially%20even%20past%20Top%20Gun's%20fictional%20Darkstar%20(which%20was%20notably%20built%20in%20partnership%20with%20Skunk%20Works)%20at%20Mach%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20type%20of%20engine%20design%2C%20which%20has%20since%20become%20more%20commonplace%2C%20is%20known%20as%20a%20turbine-based%20combined%20cycle%2C%20or%20TBCC%2C%20engine.%20While%20Lockheed%20Martin%20was%20leading%20the%20design%20effort%20on%20the%20aircraft%2C%20Aerojet%20Rocketdyne%20was%20tasked%20with%20engine%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%20billed%20as%20a%20Mach%206%2B%20aircraft%2C%20this%20new%20platform%20was%20slated%20from%20the%20start%20as%20an%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20(ISR)%20asset%20with%20strike%20capabilities.%20This%20meant%20the%20aircraft%20would%20be%20capable%20of%20carrying%20a%20variety%20of%20payloads%2C%20including%20munitions%20to%20engage%20ground%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Leland%20highlighted%20the%20use%20of%20this%20new%20aircraft%20as%20a%20hypersonic%20missile%20launch%20platform%2C%20it%20now%20seems%20more%20likely%20that%20we'd%20see%20this%20hypersonic%20aircraft%20deploy%20lower-cost%20munitions%20designed%20specifically%20to%20be%20dropped%20or%20launched%20at%20hypersonic%20speeds.%20The%20hypersonic%20missiles%20the%20United%20States%20has%20in%20development%20come%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20forms%2C%20but%20all%20are%20considered%20to%20be%20immensely%20expensive%20compared%20to%20more%20traditional%20ordnance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20immense%20pressure%20and%20heat%20inherent%20to%20high-speed%20flight%2C%20there%20are%20significant%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20insurmountable%20%E2%80%94%20engineering%20challenges%20to%20overcome%20in%20order%20to%20drop%20or%20launch%20a%20weapon%20at%20these%20extreme%20speeds.%20Lockheed%20proved%20the%20viability%20of%20launching%20air-to-air%20missiles%20successfully%20at%20speeds%20over%20Mach%203%20with%20the%20YF-12%20(a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Famericas-yf-12-was-an-sr-71-armed-with-air-to-air-missiles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweaponized%20sibling%20of%20the%20SR-71%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20Sandboxx%20News%20confirmed%20this%20possibility%20of%20deploying%20weapons%20at%20much%20higher%20speeds%20with%20Dr.%20Chris%20Combs%2C%20a%20Dee%20Howard%20endowed%20professor%20of%20hypersonic%20and%20aerospace%20engineering%20for%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20San%20Antonio%2C%20who%20has%20also%20done%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20work%20with%20the%20Defense%20Department%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20YF-12A%20at%20the%20NASA%20Flight%20Research%20Center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659bb8571c5c7b8c9a0eb184%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22860%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20YF-12A%20at%20the%20NASA%20Flight%20Research%20Center.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FDVIDS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20SR-72's%20alleged%20strike%20capabilities%20aren't%20the%20only%20important%20matter.%20The%20aircraft's%20ability%20to%20provide%20rapid%20intelligence%20over%20any%20target%20on%20earth%20would%20be%20vital%20for%20the%20United%20States%20in%20a%2021st-century%20conflict%2C%20especially%20over%20the%20sprawling%20expanses%20of%20the%20Pacific.%20Despite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fspy-satellites-arent-nearly-as-all-seeing-as-you-think%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20perceptions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20satellites%20providing%20constant%20global%20overwatch%2C%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20there%20aren't%20enough%20satellites%20in%20orbit%20to%20have%20eyes%20everywhere%20needed%2C%20and%20the%20predictability%20of%20satellites'%20orbits%20makes%20them%20fairly%20easy%20to%20keep%20secrets%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20driven%20the%20funding%20of%20a%20long%20list%20of%20modern%20intelligence-gathering%20aircraft%2C%20ranging%20from%20the%20original%20mascot%20of%20the%20Global%20War%20on%20Terror%2C%20the%20MQ-1%20Predator%2C%20to%20highly%20exotic%20airframes%20we%20still%20don't%20know%20the%20real%20names%20of%2C%20like%20the%20Northrop%20Grumman-sourced%20RQ-180.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20despite%20America's%20immense%20investment%20into%20spy%20planes%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20all%20of%20these%20platforms%20(that%20we're%20aware%20of)%20fly%20at%20subsonic%20speeds%2C%20making%20timely%20intelligence%20gathering%20a%20question%20of%20locality%20and%20airframe%20availability.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.creech.af.mil%2FAbout-Us%2FFact-Sheets%2FDisplay%2FArticle%2F669890%2Fmq-9-reaper-fact-sheet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMQ-9%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20may%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20airborne%20for%20more%20than%2024%20hours%20at%20a%20time%2C%20but%20with%20a%20standard%20cruising%20speed%20of%20just%20230%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20it%20would%20take%20a%20Reaper%20more%20than%20an%20hour%20to%20fly%20from%20New%20York%20to%20Boston%20and%20more%20than%2010%20hours%20to%20fly%20cross-country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20a%20hypersonic%20aircraft%20traveling%20at%20Mach%206%2C%20or%20roughly%204%2C600%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20could%20fly%20from%20New%20York%20to%20Boston%20in%20under%20five%20minutes%2C%20and%20make%20the%20same%20New%20York%20to%20LA%20flight%20in%20about%20half%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226c7aceac-0cde-4a4b-b5db-e83fec69da81%5C%22%3EThe%20road%20to%20SR-72%20production%20began%20in%202018%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lockheed%20SR%2071%20Blackbird%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F54885d08eab8ea5b248b456c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222350%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20SR-71%20Blackbird%3Cp%3EJudson%20Brohmer%2FUSAF%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Sandboxx%20News%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fthe-sr-72-timeline-from-initial-design-to-top-guns-darkstar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20June%202017%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20executive%20vice%20president%20and%20general%20manager%20for%20Skunk%20Works%2C%20Rob%20Weiss%2C%20told%20the%20media%20that%20testing%20was%20complete%20on%20the%20turbine-based%20combined%20cycle%20hypersonic%20propulsion%20system%20for%20the%20SR-72%20and%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20close%26quot%3B%20to%20beginning%20work%20on%20what%20he%20described%20as%20an%20SR-72%20Flight%20Research%20Vehicle%20(FRV).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20single-engine%20technology%20demonstrator%20was%20said%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Babout%20the%20size%20of%20an%20F-22%20Raptor%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20meant%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20platform's%20ability%20to%20take%20off%20under%20conventional%20turbofan%20power%2C%20accelerate%20up%20to%20supersonic%20speeds%2C%20and%20then%20transition%20from%20turbofan%20power%20to%20a%20much%20more%20exotic%20dual-mode%20scramjet%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20aircraft%20to%20achieve%20maximum%20speeds%20well%20above%20Mach%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20September%202017%2C%20eyewitness%20accounts%20of%20this%20Flight%20Research%20Vehicle%20flying%20over%20Palmdale%2C%20California%2C%20where%20Skunk%20Works%20is%20headquartered%2C%20began%20to%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAviation%20Week%20took%20these%20SR-72%20FRV%20reports%20to%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20Orlando%20Carvalho%2C%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20aeronautics%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20who%20did%20not%20deny%20the%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20I%20can't%20go%20into%20specifics%2C%20let%20us%20just%20say%20the%20Skunk%20Works%20team%20in%20Palmdale%2C%20California%2C%20is%20doubling%20down%20on%20our%20commitment%20to%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20Carvalho%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202018%2C%20another%20senior%20Lockheed%20Martin%20official%2C%20Vice%20President%20of%20Strategy%20and%20Customer%20Requirements%20in%20Advanced%20Development%20Programs%20Jack%20O'Banion%2C%20told%20the%20American%20Institute%20of%20Aeronautics%20and%20Astronautics%20SciTech%20Forum%20that%20the%20SR-72%20FRV%20was%20already%20flying%3B%20he%20then%20told%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20aircraft%20is%20also%20agile%20at%20hypersonic%20speeds%2C%20with%20reliable%20engine%20starts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20as%20the%20SR-72%20hype%20train%20was%20leaving%20the%20station%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20delivered%20an%20address%20that%20has%20since%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20modern%20hypersonic%20arms%20race%2C%20in%20which%20he%20announced%20a%20slew%20of%20new%20Russian%20%26quot%3Bdoomsday%20weapons%26quot%3B%20were%20entering%20service%2C%20including%20two%20different%20Mach%205%2B%20missile%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20immediately%20after%20Putin's%20speech%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20stripped%20any%20mention%20of%20its%20highly-touted%20SR-72%20program%20from%20its%20website%20and%20the%20parade%20of%20quotes%20from%20senior%20executives%20promptly%20stopped.%20The%20company%20did%20not%20announce%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20effort%20or%20any%20reason%20for%20a%20hiatus.%20It%20simply%20went%20about%20its%20business%2C%20at%20least%20publicly%2C%20as%20though%20the%20SR-72%20had%20never%20existed.%20In%20our%20previous%20coverage%2C%20we%20posited%20that%20this%20dramatic%20shift%20may%20have%20been%20the%20result%20of%20the%20Pentagon%20stepping%20in%20with%20classified%20lines%20of%20accounting%20and%20a%20renewed%20need%20for%20secrecy%20following%20Putin's%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20now%20know%20that%2C%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20something%20big%20was%20brewing.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20following%20year%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20191207140636%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Ftheavtimes.com%2F2019%2F12%2F06%2Fpalmdale-congratulates-lockheed-martin-on-new-facility-groundbreaking%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroken%20ground%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20massive%20new%20factory%20that%20would%20become%20Building%20648%2C%20and%20the%20hiring%20bonanza%20to%20staff%20this%20new%20facility%20had%20started%20even%20earlier%20than%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2258daf409-e2f5-41f3-b45d-9a31d82771dd%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20SR-72's%20growing%20paper%20trail%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Lockheed%20Martin%20logo%20is%20seen%20during%20a%20conference%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c656571aa2ac29ee33299f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222904%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Lockheed%20Martin%20logo%20is%20seen%20during%20a%20conference%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EMANDEL%20NGAN%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.lockheedmartin.com%2F2022-07-19-Lockheed-Martin-Reports-Second-Quarter-2022-Financial-Results%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBETHESDA%252C%2520Md.%252C%2520July%252019%2C8%2520billion%252C%2520or%2520%25246.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond%20quarter%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202022%2C%20Lockheed%20reported%20a%20%24225%20million%20pre-tax%20loss%20on%20a%20classified%20Aeronautics%20program%20that%20had%20just%20completed%20a%20comprehensive%20review.%20Three%20months%20later%2C%20however%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20filings%20indicated%20that%20the%20customer%20for%20this%20effort%20had%20signed%20a%20%26quot%3Bmemorandum%20of%20agreement%26quot%3B%20to%20modify%20the%20scope%20and%20price%20of%20the%20contract.%20This%20implies%20that%20there%20is%20indeed%20a%20contract%20in%20place%20(seemingly%20a%20fixed-price%20incentive-fee%20contract)%2C%20and%20that%20Lockheed%20Martin%20is%20unlikely%20to%20have%20to%20swallow%20these%20cost%20overruns%20on%20its%20own.%20With%20continued%20budgetary%20overruns%20now%20reaching%20%24335%20million%2C%20it%20stands%20to%20reason%20that%20the%20program's%20overall%20budget%20is%20significantly%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20the%20only%20evidence%20pointing%20toward%20a%20highly%20secretive%20aircraft%20being%20developed%20for%20the%20US%20Air%20Force.%20In%20fact%2C%20there's%20a%20fair%20bit%20of%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20that%20this%20program%20has%20matured%20beyond%20development%20and%20pre-production%20tooling%2C%20and%20is%20likely%20beginning%20a%20full%20production%20run.%20In%20particular%2C%20there's%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20massive%20new%20production%20facility%20at%20the%20Skunk%20Works%20headquarters%20in%20Palmdale%2C%20California%2C%20dubbed%20Building%20648%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20the%20hiring%20of%20thousands%20of%20new%20personnel%20tasked%20with%20building%20%E2%80%A6%20something%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F1ryvjXiZlJo%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Introducing%20Building%20648%20-%20An%20Intelligent%2C%20Flexible%20Factory%20At%20The%20Skunk%20Works%C2%AE%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EConstruction%20on%20Building%20648%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.lockheedmartin.com%2F2021-08-10-Lockheed-Martin-Unveils-Intelligent%2C-Flexible-Factory-at-the-Skunk-Works-R-in-Palmdale%2C-California%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompleted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%202021%2C%20with%20Lockheed%20Martin%20touting%20the%20massive%20215%2C000-foot%20structure%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bintelligent%2C%20flexible%20factory%26quot%3B%20aimed%20at%20reducing%20the%20significant%20investments%20of%20both%20time%20and%20money%20required%20to%20stand%20up%20new%20production%20lines.%20This%20is%20accomplished%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20explained%2C%20through%20the%20use%20of%20advanced%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20augmented%20reality%2C%20and%20large%2C%20broadly%20capable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2F41968%2Fskunk-works-factory-of-the-future-will-use-roaming-robots-to-rapidly-assemble-top-secret-aircraft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobots%3C%2Fa%3E%20known%20as%20Combined%20Operation%3A%20Bolting%20and%20Robotic%20AutoDrill%20systems%2C%20or%20COBRAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Skunk%20Works%20revealed%20at%20the%20time%2C%20they%20had%20already%20demonstrated%20the%20functionality%20of%20these%20new%20robots%20in%20the%20production%20of%20the%20technology%20testbed%20that%20would%20lead%20to%20the%20X-59A%20Quiet%20Supersonic%20Transport%20testbed%2C%20or%20QueSST%2C%20but%20based%20on%20other%20publicly%20available%20information%2C%20Skunk%20Works%20is%20up%20to%20much%20more%20than%20building%20one%20or%20two%20technology%20demonstrators%20inside%20Building%20648.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22105b2c35-c5d3-489e-a5e9-6477d90b716f%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHiring%20an%20army%20for%20'advanced%20development%20programs'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Workers%20in%20a%20facility%20observe%20a%20mechanized%20arm%20at%20work.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c65718b4912df3ae1d9a9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorkers%20in%20a%20facility%20observe%20a%20mechanized%20arm%20at%20work.%3Cp%3EGarry%20Tice%2FLockheed%20Martin%2FNASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBetween%20February%202018%2C%20when%20the%20SR-72%20went%20dark%2C%20and%20September%202023%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20increased%20the%20size%20of%20the%20advanced%20development%20programs%20unit%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20their%20aeronautics%20division%2C%20by%20a%20whopping%2075%25%2C%20hiring%20more%20than%202%2C300%20new%20employees%20over%20five%20years%2C%20with%20hundreds%20of%20openings%20still%20advertised%20on%20their%20careers%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20statements%20from%20Skunk%20Works%20officials%20that%20highlight%20that%20low-rate%20production%20of%20something%20is%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20there%20is%20low-rate%20production%20going%20on%20in%20the%20Skunk%20Works%2C%26quot%3B%20Skunk%20Works%20General%20Manager%20John%20Clark%20told%20the%20press%20in%202022.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20our%20hands%20in%20a%20myriad%20of%20activities%2C%20so%20I%20feel%20comfortable%20saying%20that%20because%20you%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20factor%20in%20specifically%20what%20it%20might%20be%20to%20then%20create%20security%20problems%20for%20me.%20But%20yes%2C%20there%20are%20low-rate%20production%20activities%20going%20on%20in%20Palmdale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%2C%20while%20the%20Skunk%20Works%20may%20be%20renowned%20for%20its%20rapid%20prototyping%20capabilities%2C%20the%20secretive%20organization%20has%20always%20been%20a%20manufacturing%20center%20for%20advanced%20airframes%20like%20the%20SR-71%20and%20F-117%2C%20once%20again%20emphasizing%20that%20his%20team%20at%20Skunk%20Works%20wasn't%20dedicated%20solely%20to%20fielding%20exotic%20prototypes%2C%20but%20high-end%20operational%20aircraft%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20really%20tried%20to%20reinforce%20that%20mindset%20that%20we%20do%20more%20than%20just%20a%20one-off%20X-plane%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20given%20me%20a%20lot%20more%20freedom%20with%20the%20aeronautics%20executive%20leadership%20team%20to%20let%20me%20grow%20Skunk%20Works%20the%20way%20that%20it%20historically%20would%20have%20been%20grown.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22afdff724-e61e-4174-b045-daf8179691c1%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20the%20SR-72%20break%20cover%20soon%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIn%20an%20episode%20of%20the%20Defense%20%26amp%3B%20Aerospace%20Air%20Power%20Podcast%20late%20last%20year%2C%20Vago%20Muradian%2C%20the%20editor-in-chief%20of%20the%20Defense%20%26amp%3B%20Aerospace%20Report%2C%20brought%20up%20the%20RQ-180%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high-flying%20stealth%20reconnaissance%20aircraft%20so%20secretive%20the%20US%20government%20has%20yet%20to%20even%20acknowledge%20its%20existence%2C%20despite%20it%20being%20photographed%20in%20flight%20several%20times%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20high-flying%20RQ-180%20(the%20platform's%20actual%20name%20is%20unknown)%20is%20expected%20to%20replace%20America's%20venerable%20U-2%20Spy%20Plane%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20RQ-4%20Global%20Hawk%2C%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Muradian%20didn't%20stop%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20another%20program%2C%20however%2C%20which%20is%20for%20a%20much%20more%20capable%20reconnaissance%20aircraft%20that%20is%20the%20product%20of%20the%20Skunk%20Works%20and%20it%20is%20Lockheed%20Martin%20aircraft.%20There%20are%20articles%20that%20have%20already%20been%20delivered%20but%20that%20there%20have%20been%20challenges%20with%20that%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20understanding%20is%20that%20the%20program%20was%20rescoped%20because%20it%20is%20that%20ambitious%20a%20capability%20that%20%5Bit%5D%20required%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20rescoping%20in%20order%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20to%20the%20next%20block%20of%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20Muradian%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThus%20far%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20further%20confirmation%20of%20Muradian's%20claims%2C%20but%20many%20see%20him%20as%20a%20credible%20source%2C%20and%20his%20proposed%20timeline%20seems%20to%20coincide%20with%20both%20the%20unanticipated%20costs%20Lockheed%20Martin%20has%20since%20had%20to%20swallow%20and%20what%20we%20know%20about%20the%20firm's%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERumors%20of%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20SR-72%20program%20may%20have%20once%20been%20dismissed%20as%20nothing%20more%20than%20flights%20of%20fancy%20within%20the%20aviation%20community%2C%20but%20in%20the%20years%20since%20this%20effort%20began%2C%20the%20technology%20required%20to%20make%20this%20aircraft%20fly%20has%20gone%20from%20verging%20on%20science%20fiction%20to%20the%20sort%20of%20thing%20a%20plucky%20group%20of%20upstarts%20can%20pull%20off%20in%20an%20industry%20park.%20And%20that's%20not%20hyperbole%20%E2%80%94%20as%20we%20speak%2C%20Atlanta-based%20startup%20Hermeus%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fhermeus-reveals-flying-prototype-in-their-pursuit-of-a-reusable-hypersonic-jet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinuing%20to%20ground%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20Quarterhorse%20Mk%201%20flying%20technology%20demonstrator%20with%20the%20platform's%20first%20true%20flight%20test%20expected%20to%20occur%20any%20day%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hermeus%20Quarterhorse%20Mk%201%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c658031aa2ac29ee332a1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHermeus%20Quarterhorse%20Mk%201%20is%20undergoing%20ground%20testing%2C%20with%20a%20flight%20test%20expected%20in%20the%20future.%3Cp%3EHermeus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20uncrewed%20aircraft%20has%20hypersonic%20aspirations%20of%20its%20own%2C%20and%20intends%20to%20achieve%20them%20using%20a%20similar%20approach%20to%20propulsion.%20Hermeus'%20Chimera%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eturbine-based%20combined%20cycle%20engine%2C%20made%20up%20of%20a%20J85%20turbojet%20followed%20by%20a%20ramjet%2C%20demonstrated%20its%20ability%20to%20transition%20from%20turbojet%20to%20ramjet%20power%20inside%20a%20highspeed%20wind%20tunnel%20nearly%20two%20years%20ago.%20The%20company%20has%20already%20begun%20work%20on%20the%20much%20larger%20Chimera%202%2C%20which%20swaps%20out%20that%20small%20J85%20turbojet%20for%20a%20much%20larger%20F100%20turbofan%3B%20notably%2C%20one%20of%20the%20engines%20Lockheed%20Martin%20identified%20as%20the%20turbine%20basis%20for%20their%20own%2C%20similar%20engine%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHermeus%20intends%20to%20field%20a%20new%20technology%20demonstrator%20each%20year%20as%20it%20progresses%20toward%20fielding%20its%20twin-engine%20Dark%20Horse%20military%20aircraft.%20Dark%20Horse%20probably%20won't%20manifest%20until%20well%20into%20the%202030s%2C%20w