dies-discovered-not-yet-identified%2Famp_articleshow%2F112688486.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fmike-lynch-yacht-sinking-two-more-bodies-discovered-not-yet-identified%2Famp_articleshow%2F112688486.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20young%20Democrats%20want%20Harris%20to%20do%20if%20she%20wins%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724255499000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F934f%2Flive%2Fe4f248c0-5fce-11ef-b970-9f202720b57a.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2Fc5yd0l1pe6vo%232%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Her%20Gen%20Z%20supporters%20say%20the%20economy%2C%20abortion%20rights%20and%20a%20Gaza%20ceasefire%20are%20among%20their%20priorities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2Fc5yd0l1pe6vo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Moon%20Was%20Once%20A%20Fiery%20Ball%20Of%20Molten%20Rock%3A%20ISRO%20Confirms%20In%20New%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Moon%20we%20see%20today%20was%20once%20a%20hot%20and%20fiery%20ball%20of%20molten%20rock%20a%20big%20finding%20being%20confirmed%20by%20the%20science%20team%20of%20ISRO's%20Chandrayaan-3.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20has%20published%20the%20first%20scientific%20results%20from%20the%20instruments%20that%20flew%20to%20the%20Moon%20onboard%20the%20Pragyan%20Rover.%20The%20landmark%20paper%20has%20been%20published%20today%20in%20the%20prestigious%20British%20scientific%20journal.%20Nature%2C%20which%20publishes%20only%20significant%20scientific%20breakthroughs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20paper%2C%20Dr%20Santosh%20V.%20Vadawale%2C%20a%20scientist%20at%20the%20Physical%20Research%20Laboratory%20(PRL)%2C%20Ahmedabad%20who%20led%20the%20team%20of%20nearly%20three%20dozen%20scientists%20said%20%26quot%3BBy%20analysing%20the%20lunar%20soil%2C%20our%20team%20confirms%20that%20the%20Moon%20was%20once%20a%20molten%20ball%20of%20rock%20some%204.4%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20soon%20after%20its%20birth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20called%20the%20Lunar%20Magma%20Ocean%20(LMO)%20hypothesis.%20Experts%20have%20theorised%20that%20a%20Mars-size%20planetary%20body%20struck%20Earth%20some%204.5%20billion%20years%20ago%20which%20led%20to%20the%20ejection%20of%20mass%20high%20into%20space%20which%20then%20coalesced%20to%20form%20the%20Moon.%20Mr%20Vadawale%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20primordial%20Moon%20was%20all%20molten%20magma%20like%20one%20sees%20in%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Earth%20with%20a%20temperature%20of%20about%201500%20degrees%20Celsius.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20India%20landed%20at%20the%20Shiv-Shakti%20point%20near%20the%20South%20Pole%2C%20it%20created%20global%20history%20since%20no%20other%20nation%20had%20landed%20in%20that%20region%20and%20it%20was%20then%20known%20that%20whatever%20Indian%20scientists%20find%20will%20be%20a%20novelty.%20Interestingly%20the%20elemental%20composition%20of%20the%20lunar%20soil%20is%20not%20drastically%20different%20from%20the%20soil%20one%20sees%20on%20Earth%2C%20Mr%20Vadawale%20said.%20Since%20there%20is%20no%20weathering%20on%20the%20moon%20the%20finding%20also%20provides%20a%20peek%20into%20the%20deep%20historical%20past%20of%20the%20Solar%20System.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fejleamgo_shiv-shakti-point_625x300_21_August_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20NDTV%2C%20Dr%20S%20Somanath%20Chairman%20of%20ISRO%20said%20%26quot%3BChandrayaan-3%20not%20only%20proved%20India's%20technological%20and%20engineering%20prowess%20by%20soft%20landing%20but%20now%20this%20milestone%20scientific%20paper%20in%20the%20prestigious%20journal%20Nature%20shows%20India%20also%20did%20breakthrough%20scientific%20analysis%20by%20providing%20the%20first%20in-situ%20elemental%20composition%20analysis%20of%20lunar%20soil%20nearer%20the%20South%20Pole%20at%20Shiv-Shakti%20Point.%20India%20is%20the%20first%20country%20to%20have%20ever%20done%20this.%20An%20exciting%20finding%20that%20opens%20up%20possibilities%20of%20creating%20permanent%20habitation%20on%20the%20moon%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Chandrayaan-3%20science%20team%20with%20Chiarman%20Dr%20S%20Somanath%20at%20Sriharikota%20with%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark-3%20in%20the%20backdrop%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Chandrayaan-3%20science%20team%20with%20Chiarman%20Dr%20S%20Somanath%20at%20Sriharikota%20with%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark-3%20in%20the%20backdrop%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Ff2rm2roo_chandrayaan-science-team_625x300_21_August_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20science%20team%20with%20Chairman%20Dr%20S%20Somanath%20at%20Sriharikota%20with%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark-3%20in%20the%20backdrop%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20six-wheeled%2026-kilogram%20Pragyan%20moon%20rover%20travelled%20nearly%20103%20metres%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20in%20the%20course%20of%20its%2010-day%20life.%20It%20travelled%20at%20a%20princely%20speed%20of%20one%20centimetre%20per%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Nature%20journal%20said%20%26quot%3BAn%20analysis%20of%20lunar%20soil%20in%20the%20Moon's%20southern%20high-latitude%20regions%2C%20performed%20using%20data%20from%20India's%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%2C%20suggests%20the%20presence%20of%20remnants%20of%20a%20former%20ocean%20of%20magma%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdding%20that%20previous%20research%20into%20the%20Moon's%20geology%20has%20primarily%20relied%20on%20samples%20taken%20by%20missions%20to%20lunar%20mid-latitudes%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Apollo%20programme.%20However%2C%20in%20August%202023%2C%20India's%20Vikram%20lander%20-%20part%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20-%20successfully%20made%20a%20soft%20landing%20near%20the%20south%20pole%20of%20the%20Moon.%20The%20Pragyan%20rover%20then%20took%2023%20measurements%20at%20various%20spots%20along%20a%20103-metre%20tract%20of%20the%20lunar%20surface%20using%20its%20onboard%20alpha%20particle%20X-ray%20spectrometer%2C%20which%20measured%20the%20elemental%20composition%20of%20the%20Moon's%20regolith%20or%20the%20moon%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESantosh%20Vadawale%20and%20colleagues%20analysed%20Pragyan's%20measurements%20and%20found%20a%20relatively%20uniform%20elemental%20composition%20in%20the%20lunar%20regolith%20surrounding%20the%20lander%2C%20which%20primarily%20contained%20the%20rock-type%20ferroan%20anorthosite.%20They%20note%20that%20the%20composition%20measurements%20of%20the%20lunar%20South%20Pole%20are%20intermediate%20between%20those%20of%20the%20samples%20from%20the%20Moon's%20equatorial%20region%20taken%20by%20the%20Apollo%2016%20and%20Luna-20%20missions.%20The%20authors%20suggest%20that%20the%20similar%20chemical%20composition%20of%20these%20geographically%20distant%20samples%20supports%20the%20Lunar%20Magma%20Ocean%20hypothesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20hypothesis%2C%20as%20the%20Moon%20cooled%20during%20its%20formation%2C%20less%20dense%20ferroan%20anorthosite%20floated%20to%20the%20lunar%20surface%20while%20heavier%20minerals%20sank%20to%20form%20the%20mantle.%20Dr%20Vadawale%20and%20colleagues%20suggest%20that%20the%20magnesium%20minerals%20that%20were%20also%20detected%20by%20Pragyan%2C%20which%20cannot%20be%20explained%20by%20the%20Lunar%20Magma%20Ocean%20hypothesis%2C%20are%20likely%20deeper%20material%20excavated%20by%20the%20nearby%20South%20Pole-Aitken%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20conclude%20that%20the%20composition%20of%20Vikram's%20landing%20site%20is%20consistent%20with%20the%20LMO%20hypothesis%2C%20which%20predicts%20that%20the%20lunar%20highlands%20were%20formed%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20floatation%20of%20lighter%20anorthositic%20rocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Moon's%20soil%20is%20not%20very%20different%20in%20elemental%20composition%20from%20the%20soil%20we%20see%20on%20Earth%2C%20the%20landmark%20finding%20by%20Chandrayaan-3%20opens%20the%20tantalizing%20opportunity%20to%20use%20the%20same%20lunar%20regolith%20to%20do%20agriculture%20on%20the%20Moon%20as%20when%20it%20is%20permanently%20inhabited.%20It%20would%20be%20controlled%20growth%20of%20vegetation%20in%20chambers%20and%20water%20and%20organic%20matter%20will%20of%20course%20have%20to%20be%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724255040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Famdhuusk_pragyan-rover-clicked-an-image-of-vikram-lander-twitter_625x300_30_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmoon-was-once-a-fiery-ball-of-molten-rock-isro-confirms-in-new-study-6387692%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Moon%20we%20see%20today%20was%20once%20a%20hot%20and%20fiery%20ball%20of%20molten%20rock%20a%20big%20finding%20being%20confirmed%20by%20the%20science%20team%20of%20ISRO's%20Chandrayaan-3.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmoon-was-once-a-fiery-ball-of-molten-rock-isro-confirms-in-new-study-6387692%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Paytm%20to%20sell%20entertainment%20ticketing%20business%20to%20Zomato%20for%20Rs%202%2C048%20crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724254570000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-04%2F1