a%20comic%20who%20centres%20her%20acts%20on%20her%20disability%20would%20be%20a%20long%20journey.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJokes%20that%20should%20have%20landed%20well%20ended%20up%20falling%20flat%20because%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20used%20to%20seeing%20someone%20like%20me%20go%20up%20to%20a%20stage%20to%20perform%20comedy%20before%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20tackle%20this%2C%20Sweta%20eases%20her%20anxiety%20by%20making%20light%20of%20her%20struggle%20to%20get%20on%20stage.%20If%20the%20steps%20are%20particularly%20steep%20and%20it%20takes%20time%20to%20climb%2C%20she%20jokes%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%2C%20thanks%20for%20clapping%20for%20two%20hundred%20years%2C%20guys!%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20the%20disabled%20one%20here%20%E2%80%94%20what%E2%80%99s%20wrong%20with%20you%2C%20why%20did%20you%20stop%20clapping%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20she%20even%20references%20a%20popular%20meme%20from%20the%202006%20film%20%3Cem%3EVivah%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EJal%20lijiye%2C%20thak%20gaye%20honge%20clap%20karte%20karte%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20She%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20audience%20sees%20me%20struggling%20due%20to%20the%20infrastructure%2C%20I%20have%20to%20address%20it.%20If%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%2C%20it%20impacts%20my%20performance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChoosing%20to%20perform%20stand-up%20comedy%20is%20in%20itself%20a%20rebellious%20act%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20term%20%E2%80%98stand-up%E2%80%99%20in%20stand-up%20comedy%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20somewhat%20ableist%2C%20particularly%20from%20a%20disability-focused%20perspective%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sweta%20muses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20typical%20image%20of%20a%20stand-up%20comedian%20involves%20a%20performer%20standing%20on%20stage%2C%20which%20can%20be%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20accessibility-centred%20narrative%20we%20strive%20for%20today.%20Gener